<div1 type="letter">
<fw type="curatorial">96</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>March 3rd 35
</dateline>
<salute>Dearest Miss Piper:</salute>
</opener>

<p>Mother always loved you dearly and you must know that from the fact that she always wanted you to have her books. I feel 
you will prize them as well as the letters he wrote his mother years ago, which I believe remained in the Bible - or am I mista-ken about your receiving it also? 
I surely hope to see you some time again - and would love to go to Wayne with my husband. </p>

<closer>
<salute>Cordially </salute>
<signed>Mona Neihardt. </signed>
<note></note>
</closer>

</div1>
